6 NEW SECTION. Section 17. Codification instruction. (1) [Sections 1 through 13] are intended to
7 be codified as a new chapter in Title 15, and the provisions of Title 15 apply to [sections 1 through 13].
8 (2) [Section 14] is intended to be codified as an integral part of Title 53, chapter 6, part 1, and the
9 provisions of Title 53, chapter 6, part 1, apply to [section 14].
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 18. Appropriations. (1) For the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, there is
12 appropriated $637,828 from the general fund to the department of revenue for start-up and operating costs to
13 implement [this act].
14 (2) For the fiscal year beginning July 1, 2025, there is appropriated $131,000 from the general
15 fund to the department of revenue for personal services to implement [this act].
16 (3) For the fiscal year beginning July 1, 2026, there is appropriated $131,000 from the general
17 fund to the department of revenue for personal services to implement [this act].
18 (4) The legislature intends that the appropriations for personal services in this section be
19 considered part of the ongoing base for the next legislative session to be paid from the ambulance medicaid
20 reimbursement account established in [section 14].
21
22 NEW SECTION. Section 19. Contingent effective date. [This act] is effective on approval by the
23 United States department of health and human services of all waivers and approvals necessary to implement
24 the assessment fee and supplemental payments as provided in [sections 1 through 15]. The department of
25 public health and human services shall notify the code commissioner within 15 days of the occurrence of the
26 contingency.
